## File Editing Rules

### Python Files
- Always show the complete file after editing
- Never add `# type: ignore` without explaining why
- Keep all existing `async/await` patterns
- Never change function signatures without checking all callers
- For background tasks: use **ARQ** (Stages 1-3), not Celery

### TypeScript/TSX Files
- No `any` types — use proper interfaces from `types/api.ts`
- For API calls, always use `apiFetch()` from `lib/api.ts`
- For data fetching, always use TanStack Query hooks

### YAML/Config Files
- Never remove existing service definitions
- Always include healthchecks when adding Docker services
- Always use variable substitution (`${VAR}`) not hardcoded values

